    <section name="Architecture">
      <p>Silverpeas functions in the Java J2EE environment. The WCM layer is used to publish public contents on the web and to build an Xnet platform, or Web 2.0 website.
        <br/>
        <img src="images/schemaMailing_mid_uk.jpg" />
      </p>
      <p>The Services Oriented Architecture is made up of:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Silverpeas Core</li>
        <li>Specific services</li>
      </ul>
      <subsection name="Silverpeas Core">
        <p>It is an applicative bus for :</p>
        <ul>
          <li>authentification</li>
          <li>rights management</li>
          <li>a search engine</li>
          <li>a workflow engine</li>
          <li>notifications</li>
          <li>subscriptions</li>
          <li>versioning</li>
        </ul>
      </subsection>
      <subsection name="Specific Services for different professional sectors">
        <p>
          Silverpeas is used to classify the contents on themes, independant of the spaces and folders in which they are stored and to for subscribing to themes.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>simplified WYSIWYG interface for editing</li>
          <li>a access to the portal via the Web browser</li>
          <li> personalised tools for the workspacel</li>
          <li>multilingual interfaces and glossairies (fr/en)</li>
        </ul>
      </subsection>
    </section>
    <section name="Operating Systems">
      <p>Silverpeas operates under.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Windows</li>
        <li>Mac</li>
        <li>Linux,</li>
        <li>with a relational database (SQL ANSI), and a Java EE application serveur.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
